<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Kongone</placeName> 5<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> August</p>
<lb/><p>1862</p>
<lb/><p>Dear <persName>Sir</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I have no 
<lb/>great objection against 
<lb/>giving an autograph 
<lb/>to a Lady but I feel 
<lb/>to be such a silly 
<lb/>thing to write my 
<lb/>name for a great 
<lb/><unclear cert="high">heanimal</unclear> like you 
<lb/>would'nt be better 
<lb/>now to spend the 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001810_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/>money you waste 
<lb/>in postage stamps 
<lb/>plaguing people, 
<lb/>in supporting a 
<lb/>poor shivering 
<lb/>half starved naked 
<lb/>boy or girl at a 
<lb/><term type="note">ragged school</term>. I 
<lb/>think one would 
<lb/>remember having 
<lb/>saved the perishing 
<lb/>with greater pleasure 
<lb/>on a dying bed 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001810_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/>than that he had 
<lb/>secured all the autographs 
<lb/>from <persName>Ham's</persName> to old 
<lb/><persName>Abe Lincoln's</persName></p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p><persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Bennett</persName></p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001810_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
